  Agaricus is the Madness Network's Australian node — 
  the central Malkavian-internal information channel for 
  the continent. The Madness Network produces intelligence 
  that is sometimes prophetic, sometimes deeply useful, 
  and sometimes incomprehensibly tangential; the 
  intelligence's reliability is impossible to assess 
  in advance. Agaricus has provided Lytton with Madness 
  Network insights approximately twenty times across 
  137 years of Camarilla Melbourne; approximately twelve 
  of those insights produced operational benefit, four 
  produced ambiguous outcomes, four produced operational 
  damage that took years to recover from. The reliability 
  ratio is a permanent operational complication for 
  Camarilla Australia — Agaricus is too valuable to 
  exclude from Primogen council and too unreliable to 
  trust unconditionally. ]

